), forewings dark, reddish, legs pale.......................... 
<taxonomicName id="36DF57C5FFFD3301FA83FAD4FAD7091D" authority="Bahder &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Helmick &amp; Bartlett, 2022" authorityName="Bahder &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Helmick &amp; Bartlett" authorityYear="2022" box="[1295,1376,1287,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Tico" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sierra" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="C3ABF054FFFD3301FA83FAD4FAD7091D" box="[1295,1376,1287,1308]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">T. sierra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="C3ABF054FFFD3301FAEAFAD5FA2B091A" bold="true" box="[1382,1436,1286,1307]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8984D2FFFFD3301FAEAFAD5FA2B091A" box="[1382,1436,1286,1307]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1602C46FFFD3301FF1BFAF7FA2B0938" blockId="4.[151,1437,1286,1631]" box="[151,1436,1316,1338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
<keyLead id="4A2E8F73FFFD3301FF1BFAF7FA2B0938" box="[151,1436,1316,1338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
1. Body pale (body yellowish-white; 
<bibRefCitation id="954E51B7FFFD3301FDA3FAF7FD5A0938" author="Bahder, B. W. &amp; Echavarria, M. A. Z. &amp; Barrantes, E. A. B. &amp; Helmick, E. E. &amp; Bartlett, C. R." box="[559,749,1316,1338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" pagination="369 - 392" refId="ref6082" refString="Bahder, B. W., Echavarria, M. A. Z., Barrantes, E. A. B., Helmick, E. E. &amp; Bartlett, C. R. (2021 a) A new genus and two new species of planthopper in the tribe Cenchreini (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Derbidae) from lowland tropical rainforest in Costa Rica. Zootaxa, 4908 (3), 369 - 392. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4908.3.3" type="journal article" year="2021">
Bahder 
<emphasis id="C3ABF054FFFD3301FDF6FAF7FD120938" box="[634,677,1316,1337]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">et al</emphasis>
. 2021a
</bibRefCitation>
, figs 4, 12), wings clear except for varied fuscous to black markings. 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="4A2B34E3FFFD3301FF1BFA92FA2B09E8" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
<paragraph id="F1602C46FFFD3301FF1BFA92FA2B0990" blockId="4.[151,1437,1286,1631]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
<keyLead id="4A2E8F73FFFD3301FF1BFA92FA2B0990" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
2. Forewing with a black spot at base (in clavus) and 4 large blacks spots distally along trailing margin (dorsal portion of wing when in repose; 
<bibRefCitation id="954E51B7FFFD3301FEF1FA8DFD810972" author="Bahder, B. W. &amp; Echavarria, M. A. Z. &amp; Barrantes, E. A. B. &amp; Helmick, E. E. &amp; Bartlett, C. R." box="[381,566,1374,1396]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" pagination="369 - 392" refId="ref6082" refString="Bahder, B. W., Echavarria, M. A. Z., Barrantes, E. A. B., Helmick, E. E. &amp; Bartlett, C. R. (2021 a) A new genus and two new species of planthopper in the tribe Cenchreini (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Derbidae) from lowland tropical rainforest in Costa Rica. Zootaxa, 4908 (3), 369 - 392. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4908.3.3" type="journal article" year="2021">
Bahder 
<emphasis id="C3ABF054FFFD3301FE4BFA8CFE470972" box="[455,496,1374,1396]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">et al</emphasis>
. 2021a
</bibRefCitation>
fig. 14, 
<bibRefCitation id="954E51B7FFFD3301FD0FFA8DFD490975" author="Fennah, R. G." box="[643,766,1374,1396]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" pagination="109 - 170" refId="ref6729" refString="Fennah, R. G. (1952) On the generic classification of Derbidae (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea) with descriptions of new Neotropical species. Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 103 (4), 109 - 170. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1952. tb 01063. x" type="journal article" year="1952">Fennah 1952</bibRefCitation>
fig 11G); head with dark marking anterior to eyes (
<bibRefCitation id="954E51B7FFFD3301FB6EFA8DFA2A0972" author="Bahder, B. W. &amp; Echavarria, M. A. Z. &amp; Barrantes, E. A. B. &amp; Helmick, E. E. &amp; Bartlett, C. R." box="[1250,1437,1374,1396]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" pagination="369 - 392" refId="ref6082" refString="Bahder, B. W., Echavarria, M. A. Z., Barrantes, E. A. B., Helmick, E. E. &amp; Bartlett, C. R. (2021 a) A new genus and two new species of planthopper in the tribe Cenchreini (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Derbidae) from lowland tropical rainforest in Costa Rica. Zootaxa, 4908 (3), 369 - 392. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4908.3.3" type="journal article" year="2021">
Bahder 
<emphasis id="C3ABF054FFFD3301FAA2FA8CFAE00972" box="[1326,1367,1374,1396]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">et al</emphasis>
. 2021a
</bibRefCitation>
fig. 13C)............................................................................................ 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1602C46FFFD3301FF1BFA4AFA2B09E8" blockId="4.[151,1437,1286,1631]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
<keyLead id="4A2E8F73FFFD3301FF1BFA4AFA2B09E8" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
-. Forewing without a black spot in clavus or series of 4 dark spots along trailing margin, markings limited to well-separated single spots (including one in costal cell, one near fork of CuA, and one in cell C3, proximad of an intramedial crossvein; head in front of eyes pale........................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="36DF57C5FFFD3301FA83FA07FA2B09E8" box="[1295,1436,1492,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Tico" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="emmettcarri">
<emphasis id="C3ABF054FFFD3301FA83FA07FA2B09E8" box="[1295,1436,1492,1513]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">T. emmettcarri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="4A2B34E3FFFD3301FF1BFA22FA2B0A5F" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
<paragraph id="F1602C46FFFD3301FF1BFA22FA2B0A25" blockId="4.[151,1437,1286,1631]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
<keyLead id="4A2E8F73FFFD3301FF1BFA22FA2B0A25" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
3. Ventral processes of first gonapophysis of ovipositor not twisted (
<bibRefCitation id="954E51B7FFFD3301FCE6FA22FC5D0A06" author="Fennah, R. G." box="[874,1002,1521,1543]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" pagination="109 - 170" refId="ref6729" refString="Fennah, R. G. (1952) On the generic classification of Derbidae (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea) with descriptions of new Neotropical species. Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 103 (4), 109 - 170. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1952. tb 01063. x" type="journal article" year="1952">Fennah 1952</bibRefCitation>
fig 11H), apex of the dorsal process angled dorsad, bifid; pregenital plate pyramid-shaped (
<bibRefCitation id="954E51B7FFFD3301FD25F9DDFC9F0A25" author="Fennah, R. G." box="[681,808,1550,1572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" pagination="109 - 170" refId="ref6729" refString="Fennah, R. G. (1952) On the generic classification of Derbidae (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea) with descriptions of new Neotropical species. Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 103 (4), 109 - 170. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1952. tb 01063. x" type="journal article" year="1952">Fennah 1952</bibRefCitation>
fig 11K).................................... 
<taxonomicName id="36DF57C5FFFD3301FABAF9DCFA2B0A25" box="[1334,1436,1551,1572]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Tico" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sororius">
<emphasis id="C3ABF054FFFD3301FABAF9DCFA2B0A25" box="[1334,1436,1551,1572]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">T. sororius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1602C46FFFD3301FF1BF9FFFA2B0A5F" blockId="4.[151,1437,1286,1631]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
<keyLead id="4A2E8F73FFFD3301FF1BF9FFFA2B0A5F" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">
-. Ventral processes of first gonapophysis twisted into near-helix (
<bibRefCitation id="954E51B7FFFD3301FCC6F9FFFBBB0A40" author="Bahder, B. W. &amp; Echavarria, M. A. Z. &amp; Barrantes, E. A. B. &amp; Helmick, E. E. &amp; Bartlett, C. R." box="[842,1036,1580,1602]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" pagination="369 - 392" refId="ref6082" refString="Bahder, B. W., Echavarria, M. A. Z., Barrantes, E. A. B., Helmick, E. E. &amp; Bartlett, C. R. (2021 a) A new genus and two new species of planthopper in the tribe Cenchreini (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Derbidae) from lowland tropical rainforest in Costa Rica. Zootaxa, 4908 (3), 369 - 392. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4908.3.3" type="journal article" year="2021">
Bahder 
<emphasis id="C3ABF054FFFD3301FC1BF9FFFC750A40" box="[919,962,1580,1601]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">et al</emphasis>
. 2021a
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 19B), apex of the dorsal process not bifid, hooked anteriorly; pregenital plate spade-shaped (
<bibRefCitation id="954E51B7FFFD3301FD76F99AFC0D0A5F" author="Bahder, B. W. &amp; Echavarria, M. A. Z. &amp; Barrantes, E. A. B. &amp; Helmick, E. E. &amp; Bartlett, C. R." box="[762,954,1609,1631]" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" pagination="369 - 392" refId="ref6082" refString="Bahder, B. W., Echavarria, M. A. Z., Barrantes, E. A. B., Helmick, E. E. &amp; Bartlett, C. R. (2021 a) A new genus and two new species of planthopper in the tribe Cenchreini (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Derbidae) from lowland tropical rainforest in Costa Rica. Zootaxa, 4908 (3), 369 - 392. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4908.3.3" type="journal article" year="2021">
Bahder 
<emphasis id="C3ABF054FFFD3301FCCBF999FCC60A5F" box="[839,881,1609,1631]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">et al</emphasis>
. 2021a
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 19A)................. 
<taxonomicName id="36DF57C5FFFD3301FB7EF999FA2B0A5F" box="[1266,1436,1609,1631]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Tico" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="287" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudosororius">
<emphasis id="C3ABF054FFFD3301FB7EF999FA2B0A5F" box="[1266,1436,1609,1631]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="287">T. pseudosororius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
